info.name: Rasgulla
info.description: Rasgulla refers to a syrupy dessert made from chhenna [cottage cheese], semolina and sugar

info.name: Rasmalai
info.description: A decadent and indulgent dessert made by soaking melt in the mouth cottage cheese in a sweet and creamy rabri.

info.name: Chena Toast
info.description: Chena toast consists of fried toast dipped in sugar syrup and sometimes topped with dry fruits.

info.name: Kesar Pista Barfi
info.description: Kesar barfi is a melt in mouth kind of a dessert filled with the creaminess khoya, flavourful saffron and pista.

info.name: Chogni Laddu
info.description: Chogni laddu is a sphere-shaped sweet prepared from gram flour batter.

info.name: Doodh Laddu
info.description: Doodh laddu is the resultant flavor of milk and caramelizing sugar while the boondi for the laddu is being fried is what gives the special piquantly sweet flavor.

info.name: Kanpuri Laddu
info.description: A decadent Indian sweet made from saffron infused boondi, cashew and almonds perfect to satisfy your craving.

info.name: Besan Laddu
info.description: Besan laddu are round sweet balls made by roasting gram flour and ghee together and then adding sugar to make a thick pasty dough that is then formed into delicious and melt in your mouth balls.

info.name: Moong Laddu
info.description: Traditional Indian sweets made mostly using lentils or flour, ghee and sugar or jaggery.

info.name: Makhan Bada
info.description: It is made by making maida dough balls which are deep fried and simmered in sugar syrup. They are beautiful golden brown in color having a flaky texture. Makhan bada recipe is crispy from the outside and soft from the inside.

info.name: Malpua
info.description: Malpua is an Indian pancake like dessert which is made of rice flour in oodles of ghee and sugar syrup.

info.name: Gujiya
info.description: Gujiya are made of sweet dumplings made of maida or flour and filled with a delightful khoya and dry mixture fried in pure desi ghee.

info.name: Kaju Katli
info.description: Kaju katli is a traditional Indian dessert characterized by its diamond shape, made with cashew nuts, sugar and cardamom powder.

info.name: Badam Katli
info.description: A popular Indian sweet mainly composed of milk, sugar and khoya and tastes delicious both hot as well as cold. It can also serve as an awesome dessert.

info.name: Kaju Kalash
info.description: Cashew kalash is a very eye catching and taste sweet made of cashews and other nuts.

info.name: Kaju Pista Roll
info.description: An Indian sweet dessert recipe made with layers of cashews and pistachios dough.

info.name: Soan Papdi
info.description: Flakey cube made with wholesome besan and finely chopped pista and cooked in divine desi ghee.

info.name: Mishri Mawa
info.description: Rajasthani dessert recipe is added with lots of sugar along with cardamom powder, pistachios, almonds and ghee.

info.name: Gulab Sakri
info.description: Gulab sakri is a traditional Rajasthani dessert made with mawa [condensed milk solids]. The addition of saffron, cardamom and rose water imparts a delicate and heady fragrance.

info.name: Laal Peda
info.description: Mathura lal peda is a divine Indian sweet. Pedas are grainy in texture made with milk and sugar and flavoured with cardamom.

info.name: Mohan Thal
info.description: An exotic gram flour fudge or dessert from the traditional ancient Gujarati and Rajasthani cuisine. It is besan and ghee based Indian sweet dessert.

info.name: Doda Barfi
info.description: Doda barfi, also known as the Punjabi milk fudge is a rich sweet made up of thickened milk and sugar.

info.name: Malai Barfi
info.description: Popular creamy fudge or barfi recipe made with full cream, paneer and condensed milk.

info.name: Big Gulab Jamun
info.description: A popular Indian sweet mainly composed of milk, sugar and khoya and tastes delicious both hot as well as cold. It can also serve as an awesome dessert.

info.name: Imarti
info.description: Kangan. Imarti is a spiral shaped crisp  and juicy sweet that is made of all purpose flour, gram flour and sugar syrup.

info.name: Kaju Katli Wthout Vark
info.description: Without silver leaf.

info.name: Kesar Coconut Barfi
info.description: Coconut barfi is a delicious South Indian sweet recipe made with coconut, sugar, milk, saffron and cardamom powder.

info.name: Long Gulab Jamun
info.description: A popular Indian sweet mainly composed of milk, sugar and khoya and tastes delicious both hot as well as cold. It can also serve as an awesome dessert.

info.name: Rose Coconut Barfi
info.description: Coconut barfi is a delicious South Indian sweet recipe made with coconut, sugar, milk, rose and cardamom powder.

info.name: Small Gulab Jamun
info.description: A popular Indian sweet mainly composed of milk, sugar and khoya and tastes delicious both hot as well as cold. It can also serve as an awesome dessert.

info.name: Thal Ki Barfi
info.description: Barfi made using mawa or khoya using condensed milk which then cut into cubes to serve.

info.name: Jalebi
info.description: It is made by deep frying maida flour [plain flour or all purpose flour] batter in circular shapes, which are then soaked in sugar syrup.

info.name: Samosa.
info.description: Traditional Indian style deep fried pastry stuffed with spicy and tangy potato mixture.

info.name: Dal Kachori.
info.description: Rajasthan style deep fried kachori made with all purpose flour and stuffed with spicy dal masala.

info.name: Pyaz Kachori [1 Piece]
info.description: Deep fried, super crispy and all time loved pyaz kachori.

info.name: Methi Mathri
info.description: Methi mathri is a savory, flaky and deep fried snack recipe made with flour, oil, ajwain, kasoori methi and cumin seeds.

info.name: Bikaneri Sev.
info.description: It is a popular crispy snack prepared by besan and spices and originating from bikaner.
